method.dox:d:
Provides an XML representation of the menu hierarchy
XML syntax:
@verbatim <menu id="1" revision="2"> # Root container <menu id="2" revision="2"> # First level menu, for example "File" <menu id="3" revision="2"/> ~ Second level menu, for example "Open" <menu id="4" revision="3"/> ... </menu> <menu id="5" revision="2"> # Another first level menu, say "Edit" ... </menu> ... </menu> @endverbatim

arg.dox:d:
An array of property values.
An item in this area is represented as a struct following
this format:
@li id unsigned the item id
@li properties map(string => variant) the requested item properties

method.dox:d:
This is called by the applet to notify the application an event happened on a
menu item.

@a type can be one of the following:

@li "clicked"
@li "hovered"

Vendor specific events can be added by prefixing them with "x-<vendor>-"
